dcterms:description: A nonlinear dynamical system that exhibits a stable limit cycle when the parameter µ is positive. The system is defined by two differential equations that describe the oscillatory behavior.
dcterms:title: Van der Pol oscillator

dcterms:description: A nonlinear dynamical system that represents a supercritical pitchfork bifurcation, characterized by one saddle node and two stable equilibria when the parameter µ is positive.
dcterms:title: Bistable pitchfork

dcterms:creator: F. Mastrogiuseppe
S. Ostojic
dcterms:description: A dataset of 64-dimensional recurrent neural networks (RNNs) used to study the dynamics and computations in low-rank recurrent neural networks.
dcterms:title: 64-dimensional RNNs

dcterms:description: A transformation applied to a system to generate a topologically similar model, involving random orthogonal transformations.
dcterms:title: Random orthogonal coordinate transformation

dcterms:description: Memory networks designed to perform tasks involving spatial memory, characterized by different architectures (v-type and w-type) that influence their dynamics.
dcterms:title: Memory networks (v-type and w-type)
